<HEAD>Convention Preparation Going Well, GOP Officials Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The $15 million adaptation of the Louisiana
Superdome will be completed five days ahead of the Republican
National Convention, leaving time to handle any last-minute
problems, GOP officials say.
   The gavel goes down Aug. 15.
   ``After 15 months of talking, planning and meeting, we're
seeing'' the results, said convention manager Bill Phillips. ``You
can touch something and see it and talk about it. It's really
getting exciting.''
