<HEAD>Kemp Says He Would Be Pleasantly Surprised By Veep Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Conservative New York Rep. Jack Kemp says
he refuses to dwell on whether George Bush asked him to be his
Republican Party vice presidential running mate.
   ``It's not your decision or my decision, it's George Bush's. I'm
not thinking about it until I'm asked,'' Kemp said when he arrived
