<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>Steelworkers Seek To Boost Dukakis Prospects</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   LAS VEGAS, Nev. _ Michael Dukakis will address a convention of
the United Steelworkers of America, either in person or by
satellite video, as the Democratic presidential candidate tries to
court labor without wearing the union label.
   The convention begins today, and Dukakis is scheduled to speak
Thursday. Although the union will express its preference, it will
not formally endorse a candidate, said Gary Hubbard, an aide to USW
President Lynn Williams.
   ``There's no question about the support'' among steelworkers for
, said Hubbard, an aide to USW President Lynn Williams. But
political analysts inside and outside the USW say Dukakis is less
than eager to be too closely identified with labor for fear people
will call him a candidate of special interests.
