<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Tokyo Stock Exchange's main index closed higher
in trading Monday, while the dollar remained steady.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues rose by 126.37
points, or 0.45 percent, to 28,326.31 points, its second-highest
finish ever.
   The dollar closed at 133.25 yen, up 0.72 yen, from Friday's
finish. It opened the week at 133.23 yen and fluctuated mainly
between 133.09 yen and 133.42 yen.
   Traders said financial issues helped bolster the Nikkei index,
which closed above the 28,000-point level Saturday for the first
time since mid-July.
   Its previous high was recorded June 17, when it finished the day
at 28,342.46.
   On the foreign exchange market, the dollar stayed within a
narrow range because of ``a lack of any market-affecting news,''
said a dealer at a major Japanese securities firm, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
