<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Victim-Wedding,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Singleton's Victim Marries 10 Years After Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MODESTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The woman whose forearms were chopped off
after she was raped 10 years ago by Lawrence Singleton and left for
dead has gotten married.
   Mary Vincent, 25, and landscaper Matthew Brockman, 23, were wed
Saturday in the presence of 75 guests, including her 2-year-old
son, Luke, the Modesto Bee reported.
   The location of the wedding wasn't disclosed. It has been
reported previously that after speaking out publicly about the
rape, Miss Vincent sought privacy in the Pacific Northwest.
   Singleton, 60, was convicted of raping Miss Vincent and hacking
off her arms with an ax after picking up the 15-year-old hitchhiker
in September 1978. She was found abandoned and left for dead in a
rural area.
   He repeatedly proclaimed his innocence and was released from
prison in 1987. Singleton spent his parole in a trailer on the
grounds of San Quentin State Prison after his planned parole to a
town about 20 miles northeast of San Francisco was met with
protests. He was freed in April.
