<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Islam     08-01 0096</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Islam,0100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Islamic Education Compulsory For Moslem Students</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government has made the study of
Islam compulsory for Moslem children, an Education Ministry
official said Monday.
   Islamic studies will become part of the curriculum up to the
10th grade beginning January, said the official, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   Minority Buddhist, Hindu and Christian children will be required
to study their respective religions, the official said.
   Moslems form about 90 percent of Bangladesh's 105 million
people. A law making Islam the state religion of Bangladesh was
passed earlier this year.
</TEXT>
