<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bus Crash,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>10 Killed in Bus Crash in Portugal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OPORTO, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An overcrowded bus jumped a highway
divider and flipped over on a road in northern Portugal on Monday,
killing 10 people and injuring more than 30 others, police said.
   The bus, carrying about 50 people, appeared to be traveling too
fast, said Torquato Beira Carvalho, a passenger quoted by the
Portuguese news agency Lusa.
   Some of the injured were thrown through the bus windows, while
others were trapped in the wreckage on the highway about nine miles
outside Oporto, the agency said.
   Most of the passengers were construction workers, some of whom
were standing in the aisle when the accident occurred.
   The bus was traveling from this industrial city to Sao Joao de
Madeira, about 20 miles south.
