<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Soviet-Armenians     08-01 0071</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Soviet-Armenians,0074</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Armenian Emigration Declines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Armenian emigration from the Soviet Union declined
last month from a record high in June, the Intergovernmental
Committee for Migration said Monday.
   In July, 1,018 Armenians passed through the transit center
processing Armenian emigrants in Rome, down from 1,767 in June.
   During the first seven months of 1988, Soviet authorities
allowed 8,052 Armenians to leave the country, compared with 2,970
in 1987.
