<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--TeenDeath     08-01 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Teen Death,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teen's Bridge Walk Ends in 60-Foot Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-ager walking barefoot on a bridge wall
lost her balance and fell 60 feet to her death, authorities said.
   Maureen Donahue, 17, of New Brighton was at a party on the Stone
Arch Bridge Saturday night when she began walking the 26-inch-wide
wall, authorities said.
   She lost her footing and fell.
   The girl's friends raced down the steep slope to the edge of the
Mississippi River, where her body was found.
   ``We got a knock on the door,'' said Daniel Donahue, Maureen's
father. ``A chaplain from the police department told us he had some
bad news. There was a terrible tragedy and our daughter was dead.
   ``I know it's real. But I don't. I lost part of myself.''
</TEXT>
