<HEAD>Jury Finds Man Innocent of Raping Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASPEN, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man found guilty of forcing his wife to
have sex at knifepoint was acquitted on sexual assualt charges
because the law on marital rape went into effect after his arrest.
   Michael Ray Engfors, 34, was convicted Friday of felony menacing
and possession of a weapon by a previous offender. The Pitkin
County District Court jury said it had to clear Engfors of
first-degree sexual assault because the law making it illegal for a
husband to force sex on his wife took effect July 1 _ four months
after his arrest.
   The Engfors had already filed for divorce, and Kim Engfors said
her husband, carrying a knife, went into her room and demanded sex,
which she refused.
   Engfors faces one to four years in jail. The marital rape charge
carries a minimum 20-year sentence.
