<1ST_LINE>r a AM-CaughtWatering     08-01 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Caught Watering,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>City Hall Lawn Watered On Wrong Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Officials at City Hall had reason to blush
a little Monday. A radio reporter caught them watering the lawn on
the wrong day.
   For several months, the city has restricted lawn sprinkling
because of problems in the water distribution system. Even-numbered
addresses are allowed to water on even-numbered days while those
with odd-numbered addresses can do so on the opposite days.
   Well, City Hall is located at 200 N. Walker Ave. _ an
even-numbered address.
   And Monday was Aug. 1 _ an odd number.
   But for much of the morning, a sprinkler was running on the City
Hall lawn.
   City spokeswoman Karen Farney acknowledged the mistake.
   She told radio station KOMA-AM the sprinkler will be left off
Tuesday to make up for the error.
   And she acknowledged that the city was not setting the best of
examples.
</TEXT>
