<DATELINE>OPORTO, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus packed with construction workers
jumped a highway divider and flipped over Monday on a highway in
northern Portugal, killing eight people and injuring 54 others,
police said.
   A police traffic brigade spokesman in the capital, Lisbon, said
the bus was carrying the workers to a construction site when it
crashed about nine miles outside Oporto. The official spoke on
conditon of anonymity.
   The Portuguese news agency Lusa said the legal capacity of the
bus was 52 passengers but extra passengers reportedly were standing
in the aisle.
   Earlier, police said at least 10 people were killed. Police gave
no explanation for the change in the death toll.
   The bus appeared to be traveling too fast, said Torquato Beira
Carvalho, a passenger quoted by the Portuguese news agency Lusa.
   Some of the injured were thrown through the bus windows, while
others were trapped in the wreckage, the agency said.
   The bus was traveling from Oporto to Sao Joao de Madeira, about
20 miles south.
