<HEAD>Floods Kill 214 in Eastern China</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates figures on casualties, damages, editing throughout</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Floods in eastern China's Zhejiang province
claimed at least 214 lives and 449 people are missing, the official
China Daily newspaper reported Monday.
   It said torrential rains caused flooding Friday and Saturday
that left thousands of people homeless.
   The newspaper quoted a provincial official as saying 16,949
houses, 305 bridges and 100 reservoirs were destroyed. It said he
placed economic losses at $167 million.
   The deaths brought to at least 750 the number of Chinese
reported to have perished in floods this year. Hundreds of others
have died from heat-related causes in one of the hottest summers in
years in central and southern China where there are water and food
shortages from a prolonged drought.
