   A measured approach to the market could mean better things down
the road. ``That's the kind of action you get prior to a trend
resuming,'' Wachtel said.
   Market watchers have been reluctant to proclaim that the Dow's
summer rally was back on track despite its 68-point surge last
week, the key barometer's biggest weekly gain since April.
   Among actively traded Big Board issues, IBM was up ] at 126[,
American Express was up } at 28~, Exxon was down ] at 47, and
Eastman Kodak was unchanged at 45|.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
0.03 to 153.32. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index stood at 306.47, up 0.29.
   On Friday the Dow Jones industrial average climbed 46.60 to
2,128.73.
   Gaining issues outnumbered declines by about 15 to 4 on the
NYSE, with 1,178 up, 329 down and 470 unchanged. Big Board volume
totaled 192.34 million shares, against 154.57 million shares in the
previous session.
