<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market remained firm today despite
selling pressure after last week's sharp gains.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which surged 46 points
on Friday, was up 1.96 at 2,130.69 an hour before the closing bell.
   Gainers outpaced losers by about 8 to 7 in the overall tally of
New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 755 issues up, 662 down
and 512 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 120.02 million shares as of 3
p.m. on Wall Street.
   Stock prices seesawed slightly after a mixed opening but managed
to hold their ground. Analysts were encouraged by the restrained
approach to equities.
   ``This is extremely healthy,'' said Philip Puccio, a senior vice
president at Dillon, Read & Co. ``The market really hasn't given up
much ground.''
   Analysts said they would have been far more concerned had the
market opened on a strong note and built too quickly on last week's
gains.
   ``What you don't want to see is instant euphoria,'' said Larry
Wachtel, first vice president at Prudential-Bache Securities Inc.
   A measured approach to the market could mean better things down
the road. ``That's the kind of action you get prior to a trend
resuming,'' Wachtel said.
   Market watchers have been reluctant to proclaim the Dow's summer
rally back on track despite its 68-point surge last week, the key
barometer's biggest weekly gain since April.
   But with traders and institutions taking some profits today,
Puccio said the market likely is being positioned to move higher
later in the week since underlying sentiment remains positive.
   Among actively traded Big Board issues, Gillette was down 2{ at
37|; the razor blade maker settled its legal dispute with Consiton
Partners and will buy back 16 million shares for $45 each.
   Boeing, which reported higher quarterly earnings, was up 1~ at
62]. Central & South West, the most active issue with 19.7 million
shares changing hands, was up \ at 31|. Traders were interested in
capturing the utility's dividend.
   Elsewhere, IBM was up \ at 126, American Express was up 1 at
29[, and Mead Corp. was off 1] at 41~.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
0.02 to 153.37. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index stood at 306.38, up 0.20.
