<HEAD>Steel Output Up 3.1 Percent Last Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.965 million tons in
the week ended July 30, an increase of 3.1 percent from the
previous week's 1.905 million tons, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 92.1 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 89.3 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
58.547 million net tons, an increase of 20.4 percent from the
48.626 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 90.2 percent of capacity,
compared with 75.0 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended July 30: Northeast
Coast, 271,000; Pittsburgh, 197,000; Youngstown, 123,000; Lake
Erie, 169,000; Detroit, 157,000; Chicago, 195,000; Midwest,
531,000; Southern, 224,000; and Western, 98,000.
