from 1,377.75; 1.2075 Canadian dollars, down from 1.2105
   Gold fell in London to a bid price of $433.75 a troy ounce, down
from late Friday's $435.25. The metals market in Zurich,
Switzerland, was closed for a national holiday.
   Earlier, in Hong Kong, gold fell 87 cents a troy ounce to close
at a bid of $436.70.
   On the Commodity Exchange in New York, gold for August delivery
closed at $434.40 a troy ounce, down from $436.10 late Friday.
