<1ST_LINE>d f BC-USG-MetalBusinesses     08-01 0121</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-USG-Metal Businesses,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>USG Corporation Announces Plans To Sell Metal Businesses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USG Corp. said Monday it plans to sell four
construction metal and steel framing facilities to help pay off
debt incurred in its recapitalization.
   The plants to be sold are in Boonton, N.J.; Morrow, Ga.;
Mansfield, Tex.; and Franklin Park, Ill., Chicago-based USG said in
a statement.
   The facilities employ about 400 people and generate more than
$100 million in annual sales, the statement read.
   USG also will relocate a Torrance, Calif., facility as part of
the plan.
   The planned sale is part of USG's recapitalization and
restructuring, in which the corporation is focusing its resources
on its core businesses, such as gypsum and gypsum-related products.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
